{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The request sent to the external API always includes the complete list of valid taxonomy labels.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is request construction plus adapter wiring. A unit test of a helper can miss dropped labels caused by serializer/adapter integration, while a full real API call is not required to catch this class of bug.","test_description":"Wire the classifier module to the real request-building path and a capture stub transport (in-process test double at the API boundary). Invoke classify() and assert the outbound payload contains every taxonomy label exactly once.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When the API returns a label that is not in the taxonomy, the module returns \"unknown\" instead of forwarding the unexpected value to the caller.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is local validation/guard logic. No I/O is needed to catch a real failure: feed an out-of-taxonomy label into the response-handling function and verify mapping to \"unknown\".","test_description":"Call the label-validation/normalization path with inputs like \"medical\" (not in taxonomy) and assert returned value is exactly \"unknown\".","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.78,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The classification result for the same document is the same across repeated calls.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real model output stability. Mocked or deterministic fakes hide true non-determinism, so only real model calls can expose this failure mode.","test_description":"Run N repeated classifications (same document, same config) against the real AI model and assert stability policy (for strict requirement: all labels identical; or explicitly defined threshold). Track variance over multiple runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.08}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The number of tokens consumed for a typical document stays within the configured per-call budget.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Token usage must be validated against real provider accounting/tokenization at the HTTP/API boundary; local mocks or estimators can systematically under-report and miss real over-budget costs.","test_description":"Call the real classification API with representative documents and assert provider-reported token usage per call is <= configured budget. Fail on any call exceeding budget.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.04,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.62,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the API signals that the request rate is too high, the module waits and retries rather than returning an error to the caller.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Retry correctness depends on real HTTP status handling plus timing/backoff behavior. High-level mocks can hide failures in status/header parsing and wait/retry orchestration.","test_description":"Exercise classifier over real HTTP against a controllable test server that returns 429 (with retry metadata) then 200. Assert caller receives success, retry count increments, and elapsed delay/backoff meets policy.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.06,"Integration":0.35,"System":0.55,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
